  })
  We use When or If Shards to create a conditional statement and do an action when the Predicate parameter returns true. 
  To chain more conditions to the Predicate we use the And Shard. With conditions chained by the And Shard, the Predicate parameter will only
  return true when all conditions are met.
  #General

 [element1 element2 element3]
 | ForEach({
  Math.Add(1)
 })

  [element1 element2 element3]
 | ForEach(Apply:{
  Math.Add(1)
 })

  For each, processes every element or key-value pair of a sequence/table with a given Shard or sequence of Shards. In the example provided in the solution,
  we will add 1 to element1 then element2 and element3. The ForEach Shard will return its input as its output.
  #General

 variable1
 If(Is(true) {
  Pass ;Do Something
 } {
  Pass ; Else do something else
 })

  Get(variable1)
  If(Predicate:Is(Value: true) Then:{
    Pass ;Do Something
  } Else:{
    Pass ;Do Something else
  })

  The If Shard is a Shard used to create a conditional statement. If the conditions stated in the Predicate parameter is met, it will execute what is stated in
  the Then paramater. If the condition is not met, it will execute what is listed in the Else parameter.
  #General

